gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 127, Pacers 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Pacers, 127-109. Karl-Anthony Towns recorded a season-high 40 points, along with 12 rebounds for the Timberwolves, while Anthony Edwards added 37 points and 7 3PM in the victory. Bruce Brown tallied 17 points and five rebounds for the Pacers in the losing effort. The Timberwolves improve to 19-5 on the season, while the Pacers fall to 13-11.
